- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of hypertree decompositions in solving computation problems, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as hypertree decompositions are a topic in discrete mathematics and combinatorics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the tractability of computation problems based on the hypertree-width of hypergraphs. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as hypertree decompositions have applications in geometric algorithms and computational geometry.
